<subSubSection id="C309EEC62F6CFFE74EAFFEBEFCEFFDF3" pageId="22" pageNumber="173" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BACBD4D2F6CFFE74EAFFEBEFE6CFE2B" blockId="22.[151,1436,222,607]" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6CFFE74EAFFEBEFD9EFEB7" bold="true" box="[199,577,258,283]" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">Pertinent taxonomic references.</emphasis>
Müller (1923), Noble (1923), Mertens (1925), Ruibal (1952), 
<collectingCountry id="F304FDDD2F6CFFE74A93FEBEFA9BFEB7" box="[1275,1348,258,283]" name="Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">Cunha</collectingCountry>
(1961), Uzzell &amp; Barry (1971), Hoogmoed (1973), Ávila-Pires (1995), Pellegrino 
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6CFFE74D8BFE9BFBC3FE93" box="[995,1052,294,319]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">et al.</emphasis>
(2001, 2003, 2011), Rodrigues &amp; Ávila-Pires (2005), Castoe 
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6CFFE74FB1FEF0FDC9FECF" box="[473,534,330,355]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">et al.</emphasis>
(2004), Laguna 
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6CFFE74C89FEF0FCC0FECF" box="[737,799,330,355]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">et al.</emphasis>
(2010), Rodrigues 
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6CFFE74A60FEF0FBE2FECF" box="[1032,1085,330,355]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">et al</emphasis>
. (2013), Souza 
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6CFFE74B69FEF0FAE9FECF" box="[1281,1334,330,355]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">et al</emphasis>
. (2015), Goicoechea 
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6CFFE74F4AFED3FE8CFE2B" box="[290,339,366,391]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">et al</emphasis>
. (2016).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BACBD4D2F6CFFE74EAFFE2EFCEFFDF3" blockId="22.[151,1436,222,607]" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6CFFE74EAFFE2EFE60FE07" bold="true" box="[199,447,402,427]" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">Taxonomic remarks.</emphasis>
This is an unisexual lizard, of which both diploid and triploid populations are known, representing at least two independent lineages (Pellegrino 
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6CFFE74D44FE0BFCBAFE63" box="[812,869,438,463]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">et al.</emphasis>
2011). Recently, Souza 
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6CFFE74A12FE0BFB73FE63" box="[1146,1196,438,463]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">et al</emphasis>
. (2015) reported and described the first known males attributed to the species from two localities in northwestern 
<taxonomicName id="4C13C6CE2F6CFFE74AC5FE66FAFBFE5F" box="[1197,1316,474,499]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Meliolaceae" genus="Amazonia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Meliolales" pageId="22" pageNumber="195" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Amazonia</taxonomicName>
. The same authors did not find morphological differences between unisexual and the specimens from that localities, and suggested that the origin of parthenogenesis in 
<taxonomicName id="4C13C6CE2F6CFFE74CC3FD98FCBFFD97" authority="Cope, 1868" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1868" box="[683,864,548,571]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="22" pageNumber="173" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="percarinatum">
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6CFFE74CC3FD98FCBFFD97" box="[683,864,548,571]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">L. percarinatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
probably occurred on northern 
<taxonomicName id="4C13C6CE2F6CFFE74AAFFD9EFAE5FD97" box="[1223,1338,546,571]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Meliolaceae" genus="Amazonia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Meliolales" pageId="22" pageNumber="195" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Amazonia</taxonomicName>
near the area where the sexually dimorphic populations were found.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF6CEDC52F6CFFE74EFFF836FB25F80C" box="[151,1274,1930,1952]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/581989/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="173" targetBox="[154,1434,672,1899]" targetPageId="22">
<paragraph id="8BACBD4D2F6CFFE74EFFF836FB25F80C" blockId="22.[151,1274,1930,1952]" box="[151,1274,1930,1952]" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6CFFE74EFFF836FEC0F833" bold="true" box="[151,287,1930,1952]" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">FIGURE 14.</emphasis>
Distribution of examined material of 
<taxonomicName id="4C13C6CE2F6CFFE74CF7F836FC40F80C" authority="Cope, 1868" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1868" box="[671,927,1930,1952]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="22" pageNumber="173" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="percarinatum">
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6CFFE74CF7F836FC40F80C" box="[671,927,1930,1952]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">Loxopholis percarinatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C13C6CE2F6CFFE74DB8F836FB2AF80C" box="[976,1269,1930,1952]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Micrablepharus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="22" pageNumber="173" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maximiliani">Micrablepharus maximiliani</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C309EEC62F6DFFE64EAFFF2BFE49FE00" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BACBD4D2F6DFFE64EAFFF2BFE49FE00" blockId="23.[151,1437,151,429]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6DFFE64EAFFF2BFE2FFF1C" bold="true" box="[199,496,151,176]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Distribution and habitat.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C13C6CE2F6DFFE64F9FFF2BFCCEFF1C" authority="Cope, 1868" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1868" box="[503,785,151,176]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="percarinatum">
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6DFFE64F9FFF2BFCCEFF1C" box="[503,785,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Loxopholis percarinatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to, and widespread in, 
<taxonomicName id="4C13C6CE2F6DFFE64AFBFF2BFAD6FF1C" box="[1171,1289,151,176]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Meliolaceae" genus="Amazonia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Meliolales" pageId="23" pageNumber="195" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Amazonia</taxonomicName>
, occurring in 
<collectingCountry id="F304FDDD2F6DFFE64EFFFF00FF01FF79" box="[151,222,188,213]" name="Brazil" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F304FDDD2F6DFFE64E82FF00FE87FF79" box="[234,344,188,213]" name="Suriname" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Suriname</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F304FDDD2F6DFFE64F0DFF00FE60FF78" box="[357,447,188,212]" name="Guyana" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Guyana</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F304FDDD2F6DFFE64FA3FF00FD9EFF79" box="[459,577,188,213]" name="Venezuela" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="F304FDDD2F6DFFE64C15FF01FD6FFF78" box="[637,688,189,212]" name="Peru" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="1328A1C82F6DFFE64CA8FF00FCCAFF78" box="[704,789,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1930,1952]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,672,1899]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[151,1436,662,1908]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 14. Distribution of examined material of Loxopholis percarinatum and Micrablepharus maximiliani." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/581989/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). Aguayo &amp; Muñoz (2008) also reported it from 
<collectingCountry id="F304FDDD2F6DFFE64B2BFF00FA46FF79" box="[1347,1433,188,213]" name="Bolivia" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
. In 
<collectingCountry id="F304FDDD2F6DFFE64EDFFF63FF21FF54" box="[183,254,223,248]" name="Brazil" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, it is known from the states of 
<collectingRegion id="49D773AF2F6DFFE64C0BFF5CFD68FF54" box="[611,695,224,248]" country="Brazil" name="Amapa" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Amapá</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49D773AF2F6DFFE64CABFF5CFD27FF54" box="[707,760,224,248]" country="Suriname" name="Para" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Pará</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49D773AF2F6DFFE64D6DFF63FCA6FF54" box="[773,889,223,248]" country="Brazil" name="Maranhao" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Maranhão</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49D773AF2F6DFFE64DEEFF63FC2AFF54" box="[902,1013,223,248]" country="Brazil" name="Tocantins" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Tocantins</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49D773AF2F6DFFE64A69FF5CFBA5FF54" box="[1025,1146,224,248]" country="Venezuela" name="Amazonas" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Amazonas</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49D773AF2F6DFFE64AEFFF63FB35FF54" box="[1159,1258,223,248]" country="Brazil" name="Roraima" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Roraima</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49D773AF2F6DFFE64A9FFF63FAB8FF54" box="[1271,1383,223,248]" country="Brazil" name="Rondonia" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Rondônia</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion id="49D773AF2F6DFFE64EFFFEB9FEF1FEB0" box="[151,302,260,284]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Mato Grosso</collectingRegion>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C13C6CE2F6DFFE64F52FEB8FD88FEB0" authority="Cope, 1868" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1868" box="[314,599,260,285]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="percarinatum">
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6DFFE64F52FEB8FD88FEB0" box="[314,599,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Loxopholis percarinatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is terrestrial and diurnal, inhabits primary and secondary terra firme and flooded (varzea) forests, and swampy areas, where it is found among leaf litter (Vitt 
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6DFFE64A2AFE95FBA5FEEC" box="[1090,1146,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">et al.</emphasis>
1999; Molina 
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6DFFE64B76FE95FA8AFEEC" box="[1310,1365,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">et al.</emphasis>
2004; Barrio-Amorós 
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6DFFE64F21FEF1FEA6FEC9" box="[329,377,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">et al</emphasis>
. 2011; Waldez 
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6DFFE64C4FFEF1FD80FEC9" box="[551,607,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">et al.</emphasis>
2013). Even though it occurs in a variety of environments, it is frequently found along shaded water edges (
<collectingCountry id="F304FDDD2F6DFFE64C73FED3FDB9FE24" box="[539,614,367,392]" name="Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Cunha</collectingCountry>
1961; Hoogmoed 1973; Martins 1991b; Ávila-Pires 1995; Vitt &amp; Zani 1998; Vitt 
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6DFFE64F66FE29FE98FE01" box="[270,327,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">et al.</emphasis>
2008).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
